View list of imported controlled vocabularies

 

The administrator is able to view the list of imported from excel controlled vocabularies in the system.

  • The user selects from the Admin menu/ Controlled vocabularies .
  • After an excel file with controlled vocabularies is imported, a list with all imported controlled vocabularies is displayed.

 

View controlled vocabulary details

 

  • For each controlled vocabulary in the list (1) is displayed:
  • The Identifier (2) and the Name (3) of the controlled vocabulary in the default tenant language (for example Name (EN) for the tenant set in English as default) - mandatory data
  • Comment in the default tenant language (4) - not mandatory
  • Extra controlled vocabularies (5) - if any
  • The Name and Comment may be reviewed in the different languages (6).

 

 

View controlled vocabulary values

 

  • When the user clicks on a controlled vocabulary (1) from the list then all the values (8) for the selected controlled vocabulary are displayed with their details (7):
    • Identifier - the unique ID of the controlled vocabulary value.
    • Name (EN)  - the description in the default tenant language. The user could select and open the description fields in all languages from the excel file (9).
    • Comment (EN) - the comment in the default tenant language. The user could select and open the comment fields in all other existing languages (9).
    • Extra 1, Extra 2, Extra 3.

 

Search for controlled vocabulary

 As there are too many controlled vocabularies, the administrator is able to search/ filter for controlled vocabulary and values instead of scrolling and browsing.

  • There are filters (1, 2) and a search field (3) at the top of the list with controlled vocabularies.
  • The string that is typed in the search field (1) is searched both in all of the controlled vocabularies details (name in different languages, ID, extras)  and in the values and their details  (name in different languages, code, extras).

 

  • Only the controlled vocabularies in which there is a match (either in the controlled vocabulary details or on the controlled vocabulary values are listed after the search is performed.

 

Setting up default system languages per tenant affects the controlled vocabularies

 

When the administrator adds or removes default system languages per tenant, then the controlled vocabulary's view pages are updated with description fields for the respective language.

NOTE: In controlled vocabulary "Language" there is only one (English) language (set as default).

When a new language is added as a system language, then:

 

 

 

  • new fields Name and Comment for the respective language are added in the controlled vocabulary details.
  • new fields: Name and Comment are added for the controlled vocabulary values of all controlled vocabularies  and the user may enter data in them.
  • If a new language is added as a system language, and there is Name field that exists in the controlled vocabulary and controlled vocabulary details, then a new field Name is not created.
  • When a language is removed as system language, then the fields Name and Comment remain in the controlled vocabulary and controlled vocabulary details.
